parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the vehicle's frame can lead to structural weakening, compromising the safety of the vehicle and its occupants in the event of an accident. It can also cause the vehicle to collapse or fold, resulting in severe injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Rust and corrosion on the frame
particularly on the underside
near the transmission mount
and around the body mounts; holes appearing on the frame; rust chunks visible and removable through holes in the frame; soft or spongy feeling when driving; vibrations while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Poor Design and Lack of Drainage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the vehicle's frame, without proper drainage holes, allows water and dirt to accumulate, leading to rust and corrosion, which can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle.
symptoms: Water and dirt accumulation in the frame; rust and corrosion on the frame; lack of drainage holes in the frame.
